News.Title: Sat Kartar Shopping: Shares Soar 90% on NSE SME Debut
News.Summary: Sat Kartar Shopping shares listed at ₹153.90 on NSE SME, a 90% premium over the IPO price of ₹81. The IPO, which closed with 332.78 times subscription, raised ₹33.80 crore. Funds will be used for acquisitions, marketing, technology advancements, and general corporate purposes.
